Combine cherries, oats, sugar and salt in a medium bowl. Stir in milk, egg substitute and almond extract. Spray four 10-ounce custard cups with nonstick cooking spray. Divide mixture evenly between custard cups. Place filled cups on baking sheet. Bake in a preheated 350 degree F oven 30 to 40 minutes, or until centers are still slightly soft. Serve warm.